  "text": "For assessment of these outcomes, patients were stratified into 6 categories of readmission risk associated with their Clinical Risk Group (CRG). Developed by 3M Health Information Systems, CRGs use a hierarchical model to assign patients into 1 of 1075 mutually exclusive CRGs based on historical claims data. The average 90-day readmission rate among patients in each of the 1075 CRGs during a 5-year period determined the expected readmission rate for study patients within the same CRG. Further details about this methodology have been described previously. [CITATION_1] ",
